data.description: Welcome to your dream farmette! Nestled on 2.23 acres of lush land, this property offers the perfect blend of tranquility and functionality. With 3 bedrooms and 2.5 bathrooms, this charming home has all the space you need to live comfortably.    As you enter, you'll be greeted by a spacious living room featuring built-in cabinetry.  The living room leads to the eat-in kitchen adorned with a wood-burning fireplace, creating a warm and inviting atmosphere for family gatherings and culinary adventures. The main level of the house also boasts a separate dining room, ideal for hosting formal dinners and special occasions. Additionally, you'll find a convenient half bathroom, a laundry area, and a mudroom.   The primary suite awaits on the upper level, offering a retreat-like experience with a spacious layout, a walk-in closet, and a private bathroom featuring a dual vanity and a shower.  The other bedrooms are equally spacious, ensuring everyone has their own comfortable haven, complete with ample closet space in each.  The lower level of the house presents an unfinished space brimming with potential, just waiting for your creative touch. It offers endless possibilities for customization, allowing you to transform it into a recreational area, a home office, or a personal gym to suit your unique needs and preferences.  As you explore outside, you'll be greeted by a large backyard deck, the perfect spot for summer barbecues and al fresco dining. Imagine hosting gatherings with family and friends, enjoying the serene surroundings and the beauty of nature. As the day comes to a close, gather around the fire pit to indulge in the simple pleasures of roasting marshmallows and savoring delicious s'mores.  But that's not all - this property also boasts additional amenities for those with a green thumb and a love for animals. A chicken coop and a garden area provide the opportunity to cultivate your own fresh produce and enjoy the benefits of sustainable living. Plus, a huge storage barn offers ample space to accommodate all your equipment and supplies, allowing you to embrace your passion for hobbies or farming endeavors.  It is also important to note that the solar panels are owned and not leased.  Not only is the home itself wonderful, but the surrounding area is equally impressive. Despite the property feeling tucked away, you'll enjoy convenient access to your daily commute, with proximity to D.C., Andrews Air Force Base, and Alexandria, Virginia. Additionally, shopping and dining options are just a short drive away, providing you with a variety of choices. Target, Crafty Crab Seafood, Lidl, Applebee's, Aldi, and many other establishments await your exploration!
